name: Matriarch
description: This logo was created for the dance group Matriarch. The group performed and participated in competitions within the dance company ‘Passion and Purpose,’ which is reflected in the two P’s of the logo. Its main purpose is to be used for clothing but was also used for profile pictures, posts about upcoming events, and more.

name: Business Card
description: Personal business card for the Director of Studio 52

name: Arts & Design Exhibition Logo
description: This logo was created for an arts and design exhibition space. The design mimics the shape of an eye which represents the visual aspect of art and design. It uses simple geometric shapes and lines to maintain a modern style.

name: Sammy Hosking Mue Branding
description: This Branding was created for a makeup enthusiast (MUE) who wanted to bring her brand to life. The pink eye shape reflects makeup in an abstract way and the watercolour texture intends to mimic a makeup substance, whichever the viewer sees (eg lipstick smudged on the page or blended eyeshadow). The soft pink colour reflects the femininity and blush, which can make the target audience feel content or carefree.
